\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15429465  The ways of a foolish man are void of sense; but a wise man}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid16018931  }{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15429465 proceeds on his way aright. }{\insrsid15429465 22.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15429465 
 They that honor not councils put off deliberation; but counsel abides in the hearts of counselors. }{\insrsid15429465 23.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15429465  A bad}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid16018931  }{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15429465 
man will by no means attend to counsel; neither will he say anything seasonable, or good for the common weal. }{\insrsid15429465 24.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15429465  The thoughts of the}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid16018931  }{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15429465 
wise are ways of life, that he may turn aside and escape from hell. }{\insrsid15429465 25.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15429465  The Lord pulls down the houses of scorners; but he establishes the}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid16018931  }{
\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15429465 border of the widow. }{\insrsid15429465 26.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15429465  An unrighteous thought is abomination to the Lord; but the sayings of the pure are held in honor. }{\insrsid15429465 27.}{
\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15429465  A receiver}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid16018931  }{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15429465 of bribes destroys himself; but he that hates the receiving of bribes is safe. [By alms and by faithful dealings sins are purged away;] but by}{
\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid16018931  }{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15429465 the fear of the Lord every one departs from evil.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid16018931  }{\insrsid15429465 28.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15429465 
 The hearts of the righteous meditate faithfulness; but the mouth of the ungodly}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid16018931  }{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15429465 answers evil things. The ways of ri
ghteous men are acceptable with the Lord; and through them even enemies become friends. }{\insrsid15429465 29.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15429465  God is}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid16018931  }{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15429465 
far from the ungodly; but he hearkens to the prayers of righteous. Better are small receipts with righteousness, than abundant}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid16018931  }{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15429465 fruits with}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid16018931  }{
\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15429465 unrighteousness. }{\insrsid15429465 1.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15429465  Let the heart of a man think justly, that his steps may be rightly ordered of God. }{\insrsid15429465 2.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15429465 
 The eye that sees rightly rejoices}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid16018931  }{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15429465 the heart; and a good report fattens the bones. }{\insrsid15429465 3.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15429465 
 He that rejects instruction hates himself; but he that minds reproofs loves his soul. }{\insrsid15429465 4.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15429465  The}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid16018931  }{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15429465 
fear of the Lord is instruction and wisdom; and the highest honor will correspond therewith. All the works of the humble man are manifest}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid16018931  }{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15429465 
with God; but the ungodly shall perish in an evil day. }{\insrsid15429465 5.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15429465  Every one that is proud in heart is unclean before God, and he that unjustly strikes}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid16018931  }{
\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15429465 hands with hand shall not be held guiltless. The}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid16018931  }{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15429465 beginning of a good way is to do justly; and it is more acceptable with God than to offer}{
\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid16018931  }{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15429465 sacrifices. He that seeks the Lord shall find knowledge with righteousness: and they that rightly seek him shall find peace. All the works of}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid16018931  }{
\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15429465 the Lord are done with righteousness; and the ungodly man is kept for the evil day.}{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid16018931  }{\cs32\f35\fs32\insrsid15429465 
